686 /**

687 * Read nuxeo.conf, replace backslashes in paths and write new nuxeo.conf

688 *

689 * @throws ConfigurationException if any error reading or writing nuxeo.conf
Mar 22, 2011 NXP-6543 - Fix windows paths issues
690 * @since 5.4.1
691 */
692 protected void replaceBackslashes() throws ConfigurationException {
693 StringBuffer sb = new StringBuffer();
694 BufferedReader reader = null;
695 try {
696 reader = new BufferedReader(new FileReader(nuxeoConf));
697 String line;
698 while ((line = reader.readLine()) != null) {
699 if (line.matches(".*:\\\\.*")) {
700 line = line.replaceAll("\\\\", "/");
701 }
702 sb.append(line + System.getProperty("line.separator"));
703 }
704 reader.close();
705 } catch (IOException e) {
706 throw new ConfigurationException("Error reading " + nuxeoConf, e);
707 } finally {
708 if (reader != null) {
709 try {
710 reader.close();
711 } catch (IOException e) {
712 throw new ConfigurationException(e);
713 }
714 }
715 }
716 FileWriter writer = null;
717 try {
718 writer = new FileWriter(nuxeoConf, false);
719 // Copy back file content
720 writer.append(sb.toString());
721 } catch (IOException e) {
722 throw new ConfigurationException("Error writing in " + nuxeoConf, e);
723 } finally {
724 if (writer != null) {
725 try {
726 writer.close();
727 } catch (IOException e) {
728 throw new ConfigurationException(e);
729 }
730 }
731 }

1263 /**
1264 * Checks the java version compared to the required one.
1265 * <p>
1266 * Loose compliance is assumed if the major version is greater than the required major version or a jvmcheck=nofail
1267 * flag is set.
1268 *
1269 * @param version the java version
1270 * @param requiredVersion the required java version
1271 * @param allowNoFailFlag if {@code true} then check jvmcheck=nofail flag to always have loose compliance
1272 * @param warnIfLooseCompliance if {@code true} then log a WARN if the is loose compliance
1273 * @return true if the java version is compliant (maybe loosely) with the required version
1274 * @since 8.4
1275 */
1276 protected static boolean checkJavaVersion(String version, String requiredVersion, boolean allowNoFailFlag,
1277 boolean warnIfLooseCompliance) {
1278 String[] versionSplit = version.split("_");
1279 String[] requiredVersionSplit = requiredVersion.split("_");
1280 String major = versionSplit[0];
1281 String requiredMajor = requiredVersionSplit[0];
1282 int minor = Integer.parseInt(versionSplit[1]);
1283 int requiredMinor = Integer.parseInt(requiredVersionSplit[1]);
1284 boolean sameMajorAndGreaterMinor = major.equals(requiredMajor) && minor >= requiredMinor;
1285 if (sameMajorAndGreaterMinor) {
1286 return true;
1287 }
1288 boolean greaterMajor = major.compareTo(requiredMajor) > 0;
1289 if (greaterMajor || (allowNoFailFlag
1290 && JVMCHECK_NOFAIL.equalsIgnoreCase(System.getProperty(JVMCHECK_PROP, JVMCHECK_FAIL)))) {
1291 // greater major version or system property, considered loosely compliant but may warn
1292 if (warnIfLooseCompliance) {
1293 log.warn(String.format("Nuxeo requires Java %s+ (detected %s).", requiredVersion, version));
Apr 20, 2012 NXP-9251: split java version check into its own method
1294 }
Jul 28, 2016 NXP-20189: fix startup Java version comparison
1295 return true;
Apr 20, 2012 NXP-9251: split java version check into its own method
1296 }
Jul 28, 2016 NXP-20189: fix startup Java version comparison
1297 return false;
1298 }
